result.longName: Companhia de Participações Aliança da Bahia

assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Companhia de Participações Aliança da Bahia, through its subsidiaries, engages in raising, rearing, selecting, fattening, buying, and selling of cattle and other species, and related agricultural activities in Brazil. It also rents, subdivides, manages, and administers properties, as well as involved in the development of real estate projects and landscaping activities. In addition, the company offers engineering services and business management consulting activities; and services related to construction of buildings, and sports and recreational facilities, as well as real estate project incorporations. Companhia de Participações Aliança da Bahia was founded in 1870 and is headquartered in Salvador, Brazil.
